4. Cases in which the personal information is specially necessary for improving public health or promoting the sound growth of children and in which it is difficult to obtain the consent of the information owner.
5. Cases in which the personal information is necessary for cooperating with local authorities or the government, in executing the affairs prescribed by laws and regulations and in which obtaining the consent of the person is likely to impede the execution of the affairs concerned

Disclosure of personal information
AJJ will, in a reasonable period of time and to a reasonable extent, address any request of a personal information owner who wishes to have his / her information disclosed. We will do so upon confirming that the person in question is the applicant him/her self.

Revision of personal information
AJJ will, in a reasonable period of time and to a reasonable extent, address any request of an information owner who wishes to correct, stop the use of, delete or add his/her own personal information provided to AJJ. We will do so upon confirming that the person in question is the applicant him/her self.

Termination of use or deletion of personal information
AJJ will, in a reasonable period of time and to a reasonable extent, address any request of an information owner who wishes to terminate the use of or delete his/her personal information provided to AJJ. We will do so upon confirming that the person in question is the applicant him/her self. Upon the termination of use or deletion of personal information, we may not be able to provide the service he/she desires. We ask for your understanding and cooperation. We may not be able to terminate or delete personal information held under applicable laws and regulations.

Contact point for inquires
If you have any questions or opinions regarding personal information, please contact our information desk. Our contact details are as follows;

All Jobs Japan Co., Ltd., General Affairs Department, Personal Information Management Committee
Our office hours are from 9am to 6:30 pm, Monday to Friday.
</textarea>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-sm-12">
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <label for="TnCYes" class="control-label required">
                                Please click Yes of Application Agreement for next step.
                            </label>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-sm-2">
                                    <label class="radio-inline">
                                        <input type="radio" value="true" name="IsAgreed">Yes
                                    </label>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-sm-2">
                                    <label class="radio-inline">
                                        <input type="radio" value="false" name="IsAgreed">No
                                    </label>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-sm-12">
                        <div class="form-group">
                            <button id="register" type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block" style="opacity:1">Register</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </form> <!-- /form -->
        </div>
    </div><br /><br />
</div>


@section Scripts {
    @await Html.PartialAsync("_ValidationScriptsPartial")
    <script>
        $('#registerform').validator().on('submit', function (e) {
            if (e.isDefaultPrevented()) {
                // handle the invalid form...
                $('html, body').animate({ scrollTop: $(".has-error:first :input").offset().top - 50 }, 500);
                $(".has-error:first :input").focus();

            } else {
                // everything looks good!
            }
        });
      
        Helper.AutoFillByPostal();
        $('#register').click(function () {
            var chckedValue = $('input[name="IsAgreed"]:checked').val();
            if (!(chckedValue == "true")) {
                alert("Please click Yes of Application Agreement for next step.");
                return false;
            }

        });
        $('select[data-group="DOB"]').change(function (item) {
            var year = $('#BirthYear').val();
            var month = $('#BirthMonth').val()
            var day = $('#BirthDay').val();
            if (day != "Day" && year != "Year" && month != "Month") {
                var dobString = $('#BirthYear').val() + "-" + $('#BirthMonth').val() + '-' + $('#BirthDay').val();
                $('#Age').val(getAge(dobString));
            }
        });

        $('#VisaType').change(function () {
            $.getJSON("@Url.Action("GetSubVisa", "Home")", { parentId: $(this).val() }, function (data) {
                $('#dvSubVisaType').hide();
                $('#dvPermitToWork').hide();
                console.log(data);
                if (data.length > 1) {
                    $('#dvSubVisaType').show();
                    $('#SubVisaType').empty();
                    $('#SubVisaType').append("<option value=''>--Choose Category --</option>");
                    $.each(data, function (index, value) {
                        $('#SubVisaType').append("<option data-needpermission="+value["needPermission"]+" value='" + value["id"] + "'>" + value["subCategory"] + "</option>");
                    });
                }
                else if (data.length === 1) {
                    $('#VisaTypeId').val(data[0].id)
                    console.log(data[0].needPermission);
                    if (data[0].needPermission === 'Y') {
                        $('#dvPermitToWork').show();
                        //$('#yespermitted').val(true).trigger("click");
                    }
                    else {
                        $('#dvPermitToWork').hide();
                    }

                }

            });

        });

        $('#SubVisaType').on('change', function () {
            var visatypeid = $(this).val();
            $('#VisaTypeId').val(visatypeid);
            var needPermission = $('option:selected', this).attr('data-needpermission');
            if (needPermission == 'Y') {
                $('#dvPermitToWork').show();
            }
            else {
                $('#dvPermitToWork').hide();
            }

        });

        $('input[name="InJapan"]').change(function (item) {
            if (item.target.value != "Y") { //when not in japan
                $('#OtherCountryDiv').show();
                $('#InjapanDiv').hide();

            }
            else { // when in japan
                $('#OtherCountryDiv').hide();
                $('#InjapanDiv').show();

            }

        });

        $('input[name="IsRememberPostal"]').change(function (item) {
            if (item.target.value != "Y") { //when postal code is optional
                $('label[for="postalAddress"]').removeClass('required');
                $('#postalAddress1').removeAttr('required');
                $('#postalAddress2').removeAttr('required');
                $('#ProvinceID').prop('readonly', false);
                $('#ProvinceID').attr("style", "pointer-events: auto;background-color:#fff");
                $('#CityName').prop('readonly', false);
                $('#Town').prop('readonly', false);

            }
            else { //when postal code is mandatary
                $('label[for="postalAddress"]').addClass('required');
                $('#postalAddress1').attr('required', true);
                $('#postalAddress2').attr('required', true);
                $('#ProvinceID').prop('readonly', true);
                $('#ProvinceID').attr("style", "pointer-events: none;background-color:#eee");
                $('#CityName').prop('readonly', true);
                $('#Town').prop('readonly', true);

            }

        });

        function getAge(dateString) {
            var today = new Date();
            var birthDate = new Date(dateString);
            var age = today.getFullYear() - birthDate.getFullYear();
            var m = today.getMonth() - birthDate.getMonth();
            if (m < 0 || (m === 0 && today.getDate() < birthDate.getDate())) {
                age--;
            }
            return age;
        }
    </script>

}